text: Killagh is a civil parish in County Westmeath, Ireland. It is located about east–north–east of Mullingar. Killagh is one of 7 civil parishes in the barony of Delvin in the Province of Leinster. The civil parish covers . Killagh civil parish comprises 6 townlands: Ballymaghery, Ballynaskeagh, Ballyowen, Dardistown, Graffanstown and Killagh.
